channel.description: Recent content in Photography on Jasin

item.title: Bugis
item.description: Haji Lane - one of Singapore’s more popular attractions with some lovely murals. Fun fact : my go to shop to develop film is actually in the area. It’s called Triple D and is located at Burlington Square. Shot with Minolta SRT 101 with Portra 400

item.title: Katong
item.description: Another personally memorable place, having spent my secondary school days here. Lovely quaint streets with top notch food all over, what’s there not to love? Shot with Minolta SRT 101 with Cinestill 800

item.title: Lavender
item.description: Rare place in Singapore still carrying pre 2010s vibes Shot with Minolta SRT 101 with Porta 400

item.title: Seletar
item.description: Some shots of my home for ~1.5 years, having served in Seletar Camp for my National Service. Shot with Minolta SRT 101 with Cinestill 800
